  <div class="pull-list">
    <article class="pull rv">
      <div class="pull-tag">On AI-agent trading risk</div>
      <blockquote>The first time an autonomous AI agent loses money for you will not be a model failure &mdash; it will be a <b>plumbing failure</b>. Architectures that treat the API call as the safety boundary, not the model output, will outlive the ones that don&#39;t.</blockquote>
      <div class="pull-attr"><span>Tayyub Yaqoob</span><b>AI agents · trading</b></div>
    </article>

    <article class="pull rv d1">
      <div class="pull-tag">On AI search disruption to organic visibility</div>
      <blockquote>AI Overviews compress the answer, but they don&#39;t compress the audit trail. Whoever can <b>show, with reproducible methodology</b>, where their visibility actually shifted &mdash; not just where their CTR did &mdash; will own the measurement conversation in 2026.</blockquote>
      <div class="pull-attr"><span>Tayyub Yaqoob</span><b>AI search · measurement</b></div>
    </article>

    <article class="pull rv d2">
      <div class="pull-tag">On consent mode and platform-driven measurement</div>
      <blockquote>Consent Mode v2 hands the platform the modelling job. That isn&#39;t inherently wrong, but it makes the platform&#39;s assumptions part of the result &mdash; and most teams have <b>no auditing surface</b> on those assumptions yet.</blockquote>
      <div class="pull-attr"><span>Tayyub Yaqoob</span><b>Consent · transparency</b></div>
